parameters: ...You've come. I believed you would, and I've been waiting.

You've certainly gathered quite a band of bandits, haven't
you? It was quite a journey getting here, you know?

It just goes to show how many people in this world are
overflowing with greed. Hungry enough for plunder.

How dare a bandit leader preach about right and wrong! Your
crimes are not something that can be overlooked. I will take
your life!

Heh heh heh. Don't underestimate me. My life is not
something you can take so easily.
...! (Being an oni, he truly has an intimidating presence!)
Hmm...? That sword you're holding? Where did you get it?

This is a keepsake from my father. A precious ninja sword
entrusted to me 10 years ago.
--!? What did you say? What is your father's name?
...!! Could it be...!? Are you Nakatarou-dono's daughter...?
----! Why does an oni like you know my father's name!?

...I see. So you were alive. What fate this is. That sword
was originally made by me. Long ago, I handed it over to
Nakatarou-dono. As proof, it should have a blunted edge so
it cannot cut people, right?

--Eh!? This sword...? Indeed... I thought it was
intentionally dulled, but you're saying you made this
sword!?

Indeed. To think I must fight the daughter of my friend...
Living a long life means facing such fates--heh heh heh...
It brings a dry laugh to my lips.
...(It's certain that the oni knew Karin's father.)

Ugh...! The female oni in Yotsuya also knew my father's
name. Just who are you people!?

...I will not tell. There are things in this world better
left unknown. You are the enemies of Iyegiku. Our lord has
ordered us to kill you. If you really want to know, then you
must defeat me!

Here I come, Karin--! There's no point in talking any
further!
~~~~! (First, I have to defeat this man!)

Unfortunately for you, I will claim your life with my great
sword. You, the daughter of a traitor--I shall let you fully
taste the martial prowess I've honed through countless
battles!
This is the end for you! Yaaaahhh--!!
We did it...! I definitely pierced Magara's heart!

Impressive... You must have learned the sword from
Nakatarou-dono? Your swordplay was so graceful, it reminded
me of old times...
You promised. Tell me why you know about my father!

Nakatarou-dono and I... we trained together daily in the
same village, sharing our meals as comrades. Your father was
strong and kind... a man who could make even other men fall
for him...
The same village...? My father lived outside of Edo?
Yes. That place is deep within the mountains--its name is...
Heh heh heh--Looks like fun, doesn't it? Let me join in.
You can't just blab about us because you lost, master Magara?

Aomaru... After Iyegiku died, it seems you defected from us
and disappeared... Is that true?

I got tired of following you guys around. I've been doing it
for over a hundred years. Forgive me, will you? Kekeke!

The head of the family was furious. Those who break the
rules are not forgiven... I agree with that sentiment.

Hmph, preaching to me when you're on death's door? I even
feel pity for your pathetic state. Out of old times' sake,
I'll give you a funeral with my flames.
--! Fire...! Is this the demon's ability!?
Don't come any closer, Karin! You'll get caught up in it!
See ya, master Magara--thanks for everything up till now.

Hmph... you too will soon join hell... next time, I'll make
sure to train you harshly so you don't get cocky...
--Magara was reduced to cinders and perished!

Well then, sorry to keep you waiting. You guys are the ones,
right? The ones who took the life of sister Iyegiku? There
can't be many who slay demons in the guise of a kunoichi.
Answer me honestly.

Yeah. My sister was really kind... Our parents both died of
illness, so... she took care of me in their place. She made
me botamochi every day, she was truly a kind sister.

And you had the nerve to kill such a kind sister! I'll shred
you two into rags and scorch you black with my flame strike!
It'll take a long time--!

Uuuu! No! There's so much blood flowing! Hang in there,
Yugiri-chan!

Tch... I killed the silver-haired little ninja first. The
order has changed, but now it's your turn.
You two will burn together nicely! Die--

--!! (No good! I can't dodge the attack while supporting
Yugiri-chan!)
What!? You dodged my attack...you say?

...It's been a while, Aomaru. You've become even uglier...
How many people have you killed and eaten since then?

Hmph! Not even 500! I can't live long without eating people,
can't help it! I'd prefer sweet botamochi over human flesh
any day!
We're retreating from here! Both of you, grab on!
Think you can escape, fools! Die--!

--! They got away... you say!? Damn it! Someone's stealing
my prey! Why is that guy who left the organization showing
up in front of us now--!?

Tch... Can't be helped... Maybe I'll make a grave for the
boss. As a duty to a fellow swordsman from the same
hometown...
If we've come this far, Aomaru won't follow us.
Ah, thank you! You're Momiji-san, right?

Yes. I'm glad you remember me. This is the second time I've
helped you.
I will perform first aid. Please step back...

--Momiji placed her hands on Yugiri's wounds and
concentrated her mind.
--! Amazing! The wound has closed up!

This is just first aid. The wounds you received from Aomaru
are deeper than I thought... You need to rest for a while.
Ooh... To be saved by a demon...

I don't think Momiji-san is a bad demon... She saved Yugiri-
chan after all.

Even so, I must slay demons! Many important people have been
killed by demons...! For my own... revenge...
Please rest. Your wounds will reopen if you don't.
Quiet! I will not accept pity from a demon...!

I put her to sleep with my magic. I thought it was better
than letting her get excited and reopening her wounds.

...Why have you helped us twice? Are you our ally, Momiji-
san?

My master asked me to. He said to help a girl named Karin
and repay a debt of gratitude--that's why I've been watching
over you from the haunted house in Yotsuya until now.

Fufu... I think you'll find out eventually. For now, he
seems to be focusing on regaining his strength. He also has
reasons to fight demons. Surely he will become a strong ally
and come to help us.

...(I don't quite understand, but it seems like Momiji-san
and this master are our allies... That's a relief.)
Then for tonight, this is where we part--

Please wait! Where do you live? I want to talk more with
you!

...I live in the [red-light district] to the north of
Asakusa. If something comes up, please come visit me, Karin-
san. Now then--
--Momiji vanished into the darkness as if melting away...

For now, let's carry Yugiri-chan to the ninja mansion. She
needs proper medical treatment--
This is Karin-dono! I'm glad you're safe--

Ah, the Iga ninjas! Thank you for coming to help when we
were surrounded by bandits.

We've captured most of the bandit remnants. Now the village
of Hadakanomura will be peaceful again, and return to its
original tranquil state♪

(...When I think about it, that village seemed to have poor
public order even before the bandits came, so maybe it won't
really return to a peaceful state just because the bandits
are gone...)

We defeated the war demon at the bandit fortress, but then
we were attacked by another one. I've given her first aid
for her injuries, but...

This is not good! We must return to Edo quickly for proper
medical treatment. We will carry her. Let's hurry back to
the ninja mansion.

(Yugiri-chan, are you still fighting demons in your dreams
while asleep...?)

Yugiri-dono... no, Yugiri was never meant to be a ninja by
fate. Originally, she should have been living as a farmer's
daughter in the countryside of Koshu.

Yes. There is no other girl whose fate has been changed by
demons as much as hers. And the effort she put in to become
a ninja leader was her own will--we recognize that, which is
why we can stake our lives on her leadership as the young
head of the Iga ninjas.

The temperature drops as night deepens, which isn't good for
the body. Let's hurry back to Edo--
Yes. Please help me carry Yugiri-chan.

--Karin and the Iga ninjas carried Yugiri at a quick pace
towards Edo!

--Health and skill power have been \c[24]fully
restored\c[0]!
